text: KQLC (90.7 FM) is a radio station licensed to serve the community of Sealy, Texas. The station is owned by L.C. Orrick Outreach, Inc. The station is currently silent, but previously aired a Spanish religious format. The station was assigned the call sign KCPC by the Federal Communications Commission on June 22, 2007. The station changed its call sign to KBCP on September 16, 2010, and then to KQLC on October 22, 2010. ==References== ==External links== * Official Website * QLC Category:Radio stations established in 2010 Category:2010 establishments in Texas Category:Austin County, Texas
